UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to acyclovir or valacyclovir. Dosage adjustment required for impaired renal function. Maintain hydration. Mental status changes are known to occur and may be marked, particularly in older adults or in patients with renal impairment.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Seizures, hallucinations, agitation, confusion, coma, thrombocytopenia, hepatitis, renal failure, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis have been noted. Thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura/hemolytic uremic syndrome, resulting in death, has occurred in immunocompromised patients.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage may result in agitation, coma, seizures, lethargy, and/or elevated BUN/serum creatinine with subsequent renal failure. Precipitation of acyclovir in renal tubules may occur. Patient may benefit from hemodialysis until renal function is restored.' WHERE MEDID=1;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Increased risk for developing serious infections; developing or exacerbating malignancies including lymphoma; reactivation of hepatitis B virus; central nervous system demyelinating disease and peripheral demyelinating disease, including Guillain-Barr√© syndrome; worsening congestive heart failure (CHF) or new onset CHF. Do not use with abatacept, anakinra, or Rituxan. Avoid live vaccines. May interfere with Cytochrome P450 drugs (warfarin, theophylline. etc.).', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Serious infections and malignancies, neurologic reactions, demyelination, aplastic anemia, liver failure, arrhythmia, atrial fibrillation, cardiac arrest, hypertensive encephalopathy, bone necrosis, dyspnea, bronchospasm, DVT, pulmonary embolism, interstitial lung disease, Stevens Johnson Syndrome, cutaneous vasculitis, erythema multiforme have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='No evidence of dose-limiting toxicities. In case of overdosage, it is recommended that the patient be monitored for any signs or symptoms of adverse reactions or effects and appropriate symptomatic treatment instituted immediately.' WHERE MEDID=2;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to albuterol. Can produce life threatening paradoxical bronchospasm. Use caution with cardiovascular disorders, especially coronary insufficiency, cardiac arrhythmias, hypertension, convulsive disorders, hyperthyroidism or diabetes mellitus. Use caution with MAO inhibitors, tricyclic antidepressants beta-blockers, diuretics. May decrease digoxin levels, causes hypokalemia.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema have occurred. Can produce life threatening paradoxical bronchospasm. Prolongation of the QTc interval, ST segment depression, hypertension, angina, Erythema multiforme, and Stevens-Johnson syndrome have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Signs of overdosage may include seizures, angina, hypertension or hypotension, tachycardia, arrhythmias, hypokalemia, cardiac arrest and even death. Treatment consists of discontinuation of medication together with appropriate symptomatic and/or supportive therapy. Cardioselective beta-receptor blocker may be considered, but could cause bronchospasm. Cardiac monitoring is recommended.' WHERE MEDID=3;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to Fosamax, abnormalities of the esophagus which delay emptying, hypocalcemia, risk of aspiration. Not recommended for patients with creatinine clearance less than 35 mL/min. May cause local irritation of the upper gastrointestinal mucosa including esophagitis, esophageal ulcers and esophageal erosions. Ensure adequate calcium and vitamin D intake to prevent deficiency.', INTERACTIONS='Serious adverse reactions include urticaria and angioedema, esophageal perforation or stricture, gastric or duodenal ulcers, osteonecrosis of the jaw, severe and occasionally incapacitating bone, joint, and/or muscle pain, low trauma fractures of the femoral shaft, symptomatic hypocalcemia, severe skin reactions, and peripheral edema.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Hypocalcemia, hypophosphatemia, and upper gastrointestinal adverse events, such as upset stomach, heartburn, esophagitis, gastritis, or ulcer, may result from oral overdosage. Milk or antacids should be given to bind alendronate. Due to the risk of esophageal irritation, vomiting should not be induced and the patient should remain fully upright. Dialysis would not be beneficial.' WHERE MEDID=4;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Should be discontinued at the first appearance of skin rash or other signs which may indicate an allergic reaction. Hypersensitivity reactions may be increased in patients with decreased renal function receiving thiazides concurrently. Such combinations should be administered with caution. In patients with pre-existing liver disease, periodic liver function tests are recommended. May cause drowsiness.', INTERACTIONS='The most frequent adverse reaction is skin rash which may be followed by more severe hypersensitivity reactions such as exfoliative, urticarial, and purpuric lesions, as well as Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and/or generalized vasculitis, irreversible hepatotoxicity, and, on rare occasions, death.', SIDE_EFFECTS='No specific antidote for allopurinol overdosage. Massive overdosing or acute poisoning by allopurinol has not been reported.' WHERE MEDID=5;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to benzodiazepines, concurrent use of ketoconazole and itraconazole. CNS depressant effects may be markedly increased with concurrent use of other CNS-depressants. Physical dependence with withdrawal symptoms including seizures may occur. Interaction with P450 drugs and CYP3A inhibitors. Risk of fetal abnormalities.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema have occurred. Suicidal behavior and ideation, seizures, hallucinations, mania, depression, hepatic failure, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, profound sedation, respiratory depression, coma, and death have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose results in somnolence, confusion, and coma, with reduced or absent reflexes, respiratory depression, and hypotension. Vomiting should be induced (gastric lavage if unconscious), maintenance of pulmonary ventilation is essential, IV pressor agents may be necessary for hypotension in addition to IV fluids. Flumazenil may be used for reversal of the sedative effects of benzodiazepines (risk of seizure). Value of dialysis has not been determined.' WHERE MEDID=6;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to amitriptyline, concurrent use of MAO inhibitors or cisapride, during the acute recovery phase following myocardial infarction. May increase psychosis in schizophrenics, increase paranoid symptomatology, cause shift to mania or hypomania in bipolar. Multiple drug interactions: topiramate, drugs metabolized by P450 enzymes, anticholinergics, sympathomimetics, cimetidine.', INTERACTIONS='Risk of suicidal thinking and behavior, seizures, hallucinations, extrapyramidal symptoms, coma, myocardial infarction, arrhythmia, stroke, hyperpyrexia, urinary retention, vision changes, hepatic failure, neuroleptic malignant syndrome, serotonin syndrome, urticaria, edema of face and tongue, bone marrow depression.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose symptoms include cardiac dysrhythmias, severe hypotension, convulsions, CNS depression, coma, EKG changes, impaired myocardial contractility, confusion, hallucinations, dilated pupils, disorders of ocular motility, muscle rigidity. Ensure an adequate airway, oxygenation, and ventilation. Monitor cardiac rhythm and vital signs. Gastric lavage and activated charcoal are helpful. No specific antidotes. Diuresis, dialysis are unlikely to be of benefit.' WHERE MEDID=7;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to amlodipine. Symptomatic hypotension is possible, particularly with severe aortic stenosis. Worsening angina and acute myocardial infarction can develop after starting or increasing the dose, particularly in severe obstructive coronary artery disease. Titrate slowly with severe hepatic impairment. Concurrent use with CYP3A inhibitors (moderate and strong) results in increased levels and may require dose reduction.', INTERACTIONS='Severe adverse events include arrhythmia (including ventricular tachycardia and atrial fibrillation), bradycardia, chest pain, peripheral ischemia, syncope, tachycardia, allergic reaction, dyspnea, angioedema, erythema multiforme, and hyperglycemia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='If overdose should occur, initiate active cardiac and respiratory monitoring, with frequent blood pressure measurements. Provide cardiovascular support including elevation of extremities and IV fluids. If hypotension remains unresponsive, consider administration of vasopressors with attention to circulating volume and urine output.' WHERE MEDID=8;
