UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with: hypersensitivity to sympathomimetic amines; use of MAO concurrently or within the prior 14 days; agitated state; advanced arteriosclerosis, symptomatic cardiovascular disease, moderate-severe hypertension, hyperthyroidism. May cause increase pulse, blood pressure, psychiatric events, cardiovascular events, growth suppression, seizures, serotonin syndrome, peripheral vasculopathy, visual disturbances. Multiple drug interactions. Prone to abuse and dependence.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Sudden death, stroke, myocardial, infarction, psychotic or manic symptoms, seizures, hostility, rhabdomyolysis, priapism, toxic epidermal necrolysis, and Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose induces tremor, hyperreflexia, rapid respiration, confusion, hostility, hallucinations, panic states, hyperpyrexia and rhabdomyolysis, arrhythmias, hypertension or hypotension, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea. Fatal poisoning is usually preceded by convulsions and coma. Consider gastric lavage, administration of activated charcoal, and a cathartic. Intensive care must be provided to maintain adequate circulation and respiratory exchange. Amphetamines are not dialyzable.' WHERE MEDID=11;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to aripiprazole or dementia-related psychosis. May cause metabolic changes that include hyperglycemia/diabetes mellitus, worsen glycemic control in diabetics, compulsive behaviors, orthostatic hypotension, cognitive and motor impairment, dysphagia. Multiple drug interactions particularly strong CYP3A inhibitors/inducers, antihypertensives, benzodiazepines.', INTERACTIONS='Allergic reactions including anaphylaxis have occurred. Other serious reactions include suicidal thoughts and behaviors, seizures, stroke, CVA, Neuroleptic Malignant Syndrome, tardive dyskinesia, extrapyramidal symptoms, thrombocytopenia, arrhythmias, heart block, myocardial infarction, edema, rhabdomyolysis, urinary retention.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in vomiting, somnolence, atrial fibrillation, bradycardia, tachycardia, coma, convulsion, hypertension, hypotension, lethargy, loss of consciousness, QRS complex prolonged, QT prolonged, respiratory arrest, status epilepticus. Early charcoal administration may be useful. Cardiac monitoring should be instituted. Maintain airway, oxygenation and ventilation, and manage symptoms. Hemodialysis is unlikely to be useful.' WHERE MEDID=12;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to atenolol, sinus bradycardia, heart block greater than first degree, cardiogenic shock, and overt cardiac failure. Increased risk of heart block, CHF. Not recommend in bronchospastic disease, pheochromocytoma. Use caution with anesthesia, diabetics, thyroid disease, impaired renal function, calcium channel blockers.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including anaphylaxis have occurred.  Abrupt cessation may cause angina, arrhythmias, and myocardial infarction. May cause hallucinations, psychoses, sick sinus syndrome, thrombocytopenia, visual disturbance, laryngospasm.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Symptoms reported following atenolol overdose are lethargy, disorder of respiratory drive, wheezing, sinus pause, bradycardia, congestive heart failure, hypotension, bronchospasm and/or hypoglycemia. Treatment includes removal of any unabsorbed drug: induced emesis, gastric lavage, activated charcoal. Can be removed by hemodialysis. Based on the severity of symptoms, management may require intensive support care and facilities for applying cardiac and respiratory support.' WHERE MEDID=13;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to atomoxetine, concurrent MAO inhibitors, narrow angle glaucoma, pheochromocytoma, severe cardiovascular disease. May cause anxiety, agitation, panic attacks, insomnia, behavioral changes, growth suppression. Use with caution in hypertension, tachycardia, or cardiovascular or cerebrovascular disease. Monitor liver enzymes.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioneurotic and anaphylaxis have occurred. Suicidal behavior and ideation, psychoses, mania, hostility, seizures, severe liver disease or failure, sudden death associated structural cardiac abnormalities or other serious heart problems, QT prolongation, urinary retention, priapism, rhabdomyolysis have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose causes gastrointestinal symptoms, somnolence, dizziness, tremor, and abnormal behavior. Hyperactivity and agitation have also been reported. Signs and symptoms consistent with mild to moderate sympathetic nervous system activation (e.g., tachycardia, blood pressure increased, mydriasis, dry mouth) have been observed. QT prolongation, disorientation, and hallucinations have also been reported. Dialysis is not likely to be useful in the treatment of overdose.' WHERE MEDID=14;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to atorvastatin, active liver disease, concurrent gemfibrozil or cyclosporine, pregnancy, nursing mothers. May cause myopathy, rhabdomyolysis, liver dysfunction (monitor enzymes), CNS vascular lesions, increased HbA1c and glucose. Use caution with concurrent colchicine or CYP3A4 inhibitors.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioneurotic edema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Rhabdomyolysis leading to renal failure, necrotizing myopathy, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and toxic epidermal necrolysis, hepatic failure, pancreatitis, memory impairment, confusion have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='There is no specific treatment for atorvastatin calcium overdosage. In the event of an overdose, the patient should be treated symptomatically, and supportive measures instituted as required. Due to extensive drug binding to plasma proteins, hemodialysis is not expected to significantly enhance atorvastatin calcium clearance.' WHERE MEDID=15;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with known allergy to azithromycin, erythromycin, any macrolide or ketolide drug. Exacerbation of myasthenia gravis and new onset of myasthenic syndrome. Prolonged cardiac repolarization and QT interval, with risk of developing cardiac arrhythmia and torsades de pointes, have been seen. Neonates may develop Infantile Hypertrophic Pyloric Stenosis. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, including angioedema, anaphylaxis, and dermatologic reactions including Acute Generalized Exanthematous Pustulosis (AGEP), Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and toxic epidermal necrolysis have been reported. Abnormal liver function, hepatitis, cholestatic jaundice, hepatic necrosis, and hepatic failure have been reported, some of which have resulted in death.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Adverse reactions experienced at higher than recommended doses were similar to those seen at normal doses particularly nausea, diarrhea, and vomiting. In the event of overdosage, general symptomatic and supportive measures are indicated as required.' WHERE MEDID=16;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to baclofen. Use caution with renal impairment (reduce dose), stroke patients, children under 12.', INTERACTIONS='Allergic reactions including rash, edema, and dyspnea have occurred. Hallucinations and seizures have occurred on abrupt withdrawal. Other adverse reactions include ovarian cysts, seizure, confusion, hallucinations, slurred speech, ataxia, hypotension, chest pain, urinary retention.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in vomiting, muscular hypotonia, drowsiness, accommodation disorders, coma, respiratory depression and seizures. In the alert patient, empty the stomach promptly by induced emesis followed by lavage. In the obtunded patient, secure the airway with a cuffed endotracheal tube before beginning lavage (do not induce emesis). Maintain adequate respiratory exchange, do not use respiratory stimulants.' WHERE MEDID=17;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy or adverse reaction to ACE inhibitors. Do not co-administer with aliskiren in diabetics. Symptomatic hypotension, hyperkalemia, jaundice, and cough may occur. Monitor renal function, potassium, hepatic function, lithium. Patients on diuretics may experience excessive reduction of blood pressure when initiating therapy. Concurrent NSAIDS increase risk of renal failure. Risk of hypoglycemia increased in diabetics. Fetal toxicity.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Stevens-Johnson syndrome, acute renal failure, and liver failure are also reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage is likely to result in hypotension. Hypotension can be associated with electrolyte disturbances and renal failure. If ingestion is recent, consider activated charcoal and gastric decontamination (e.g., vomiting, gastric lavage). Supportive management should be employed to ensure adequate hydration and to maintain systemic blood pressure. In the case of marked hypotension, infuse physiological saline solution; as needed, consider vasopressors.' WHERE MEDID=18;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to benzonatate.', INTERACTIONS='Severe hypersensitivity reactions including bronchospasm, laryngospasm and cardiovascular collapse have been reported. Other adverse reactions include bizarre behavior with mental confusion and visual hallucinations.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Symptoms of overdose include restlessness and tremors which may proceed to clonic convulsions followed by profound CNS depression. Convulsions, coma, cerebral edema and cardiac arrest have been reported within one hour of ingestion. Evacuate gastric contents and administer copious amounts of activated charcoal slurry. Protection against aspiration. Intensive support of respiration and cardiovascular-renal function. Do not use CNS stimulants.' WHERE MEDID=19;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to benztropine and under 3 years old. May cause heat intolerance, glaucoma (may precipitate acute angle closure),', INTERACTIONS='Allergic reactions including rash have occurred. Other serious reactions include paralytic ileus, hyperthermia, heat stroke, urinary retention, hallucinations, extrapyramidal symptoms, tardive dyskinesia, toxic psychosis.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose symptoms are similar to atropine or antihistamine overdosage: CNS depression, stimulation; confusion; nervousness; intensification of mental symptoms or toxic psychosis; hyperthermia : hot, dry, flushed skin; delirium; coma; shock; convulsions. Induce emesis or perform gastric lavage. Physostigmine salicylate, 1 to 2 mg, SC or IV, reportedly will reverse symptoms of anticholinergic intoxication. Otherwise treatment is symptomatic and supportive. Maintain respiration.' WHERE MEDID=20;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to budesonide. Hypercorticism and adrenal suppression may occur. Increased risk of infection, more serious or even fatal course. Use caution in impaired hepatic function, with concurrent ketoconazole or ingestion of grapefruit. Gastric acid reduction inhibits absorption.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including anaphylaxis have occurred. Intracranial hypertension, increased blood pressure, cataracts, glaucoma, and immunosuppression with fulminant infections have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Treatment consists of immediate gastric lavage or emesis followed by supportive and symptomatic therapy. Chronic overdosage may result in signs/symptoms of hypercorticism and adrenal suppression.' WHERE MEDID=21;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to budesonide/formoterol or as primary treatment for status asthmaticus or acute episodes of asthma/COPD. Increases the risk of asthma-related deaths. Can produce life threatening paradoxical bronchospasm.  Immunosuppressive: monitor for infections. Use caution with cardiovascular and CNS disorders, cP450 inhibitors, MAO inhibitors, beta-blockers. Associated with adrenal insufficiency, hypokalemia, glaucoma, impaired growth, reduced bone density.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Can produce life threatening paradoxical bronchospasm. Atrial and ventricular tachyarrhythmias, atrial fibrillation, angina, seizures have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Signs of overdosage may include seizures, angina, hypertension or hypotension, tachycardia, arrhythmias, metabolic acidosis, hypokalemia, cardiac arrest and even death. Treatment consists of discontinuation of medication together with appropriate symptomatic and/or supportive therapy. Cardioselective beta-receptor blocker may be considered, but could cause bronchospasm. Cardiac monitoring is recommended.' WHERE MEDID=22;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to buprenorphine or naloxone. May cause respiratory depression, CNS depression 9 may impair the mental or physical abilities), liver injury (monitor liver enzymes). Use caution with head injury, intracranial lesions, impairment of hepatic, pulmonary, or renal function. Multiple drug interactions, particularly CYP 3A4 inhibitors (ketoconazole, erythromycin, ritonavir, indinavir and saquinavir).', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioneurotic and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include bronchospasm, elevated cerebrospinal fluid pressure, life-threatening serotonin syndrome, hepatitis, adrenal insufficiency, edema. Intense opioid withdrawal symptoms may occur.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Manifestations of acute overdose include pinpoint pupils, sedation, hypotension, respiratory depression and death. Establishment of a patent airway and institution of assisted or controlled ventilation, oxygen, intravenous fluids, vasopressors, and other supportive measures should be employed as indicated. High doses of naloxone hydrochloride may be of limited value.' WHERE MEDID=23;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to bupropion, concurrent use of MAO inhibitors, seizure disorder, bulimia or anorexia nervosa, undergoing abrupt discontinuation of alcohol, benzodiazepines, barbiturates, and antiepileptic drugs. May cause hypertension, precipitate a manic episode, induce psychosis or paranoia. May trigger acute angle closure glaucoma. Multiple drug interactions, particularly inhibitors or inducers of CYP2B6, dopaminergics.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Risk of suicidal thinking and behavior, ataxia, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, erythema multiforme, seizures, aggression, coma hypertension, heart block, myocardial infarction, liver damage, thrombocytopenia, rhabdomyolysis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome. Serious neuropsychiatric reactions have occurred in patients taking bupropion for smoking cessation.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose symptoms include seizures, hallucinations, loss of consciousness, sinus tachycardia, and ECG conduction disturbances (including QRS prolongation) or arrhythmias, fever, muscle rigidity, rhabdomyolysis, hypotension, stupor, coma, and respiratory failure . Ensure an adequate airway, oxygenation, and ventilation. Monitor cardiac rhythm and vital signs. Induction of emesis is not recommended. No specific antidotes.' WHERE MEDID=24;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to buspirone, concurrent MAO inhibitors or use of MAOIs within 14 days. Development of potentially life-threatening serotonin syndrome has been reported. Interaction with P450 drugs and CYP3A inhibitors. Do not use with severe hepatic or renal impairment.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema have occurred. Suicidal ideation, CVA, myocardial infarction, congestive heart failure, hallucinations, seizures, slurred speech, psychosis, parkinsonism, ataxias, muscle spasms, rigidity, thrombocytopenia, urinary retention, visual changes have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose produces nausea, vomiting, dizziness, drowsiness, miosis, and gastric distress. No deaths have been reported. General symptomatic and supportive measures should be used along with immediate gastric lavage. Respiration, pulse, and blood pressure should be monitored as in all cases of drug overdosage. No specific antidote is known to buspirone, and dialyzability of buspirone has not been determined.' WHERE MEDID=25;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to carisoprodol or carbamates, acute intermittent porphyria. Sedative properties may impair the mental and/or physical abilities. Use caution with concurrent CNS depressants. Has been subject to abuse, dependence, and withdrawal, misuse and criminal diversion. Drug interactions with CYP2C19 inhibitors (omeprazole, fluvoxamine ) and inhibitors (rifampin, St. John Wort, etc.).', INTERACTIONS='Adverse reactions include seizures, vertigo, ataxia, tachycardia, postural hypotension, pancytopenia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in death, coma, respiratory depression, hypotension, seizures, delirium, hallucinations, serotonin syndrome. Vomiting should not be induced. Activated charcoal should be considered. Airway protection and respiratory support, benzodiazepines for seizures, IV fluids and vasopressors for hypotension should be instituted.' WHERE MEDID=26;
