UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy to cephalosporin or penicillin antibiotics. Decrease dose in patients with renal insufficiency. Antacids and iron supplements interfere with absorption. Use with probenecid blocks excretion and increases blood levels of antibiotic. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, anaphylaxis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, erythema multiforme, toxic epidermal necrolysis, renal dysfunction, toxic nephropathy, hepatic dysfunction including cholestasis, aplastic anemia, hemolytic anemia, hemorrhage, and pancytopenia have been observed. Seizures have also been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Toxic signs and symptoms following overdosage have included nausea, vomiting, epigastric distress, diarrhea, and convulsions. Hemodialysis removes cefdinir from the body. This may be useful in the event of a serious toxic reaction from overdosage, particularly if renal function is compromised.' WHERE MEDID=28;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy to cephalosporin or penicillin antibiotics. May produce a false-positive result for glucose in the urine. Antacids and iron supplements interfere with absorption. Use with probenecid blocks excretion and increases blood levels of antibiotic. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, anaphylaxis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, erythema multiforme, toxic epidermal necrolysis, renal dysfunction, toxic nephropathy, hepatic dysfunction including cholestasis, aplastic anemia, hemolytic anemia, hemorrhage, and pancytopenia have been observed. Seizures have also been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage of cephalosporins can cause cerebral irritation leading to convulsions or encephalopathy. Serum levels of cefuroxime can be reduced by hemodialysis and peritoneal dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=29;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to celecoxib, aspirin, other NSAIDs, or sulfonamides, in coronary artery bypass graft surgery. Increased risk of cardiovascular thrombotic events, bleeding, ulceration or perforation, liver injury, new or worsening hypertension, hyperkalemia, asthma exacerbation. Do not use in third trimester pregnancy. May mask infection. Multiple drug interactions: steroids, anticoagulants, anti-platelet, SSRIs, SNRIs, antihypertensives, diuretics, digoxin.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include stroke, myocardial infarction, hepatic failure, CHF, edema, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis, drug reaction with eosinophilia and systemic symptoms, disseminated intravascular coagulation, thrombocytopenia, anemia, GI bleed, acute renal failure, bronchospasm.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Symptoms following acute NSAID overdosages have been typically limited to lethargy, drowsiness, nausea, vomiting, and epigastric pain. No specific antidotes. Consider emesis and/or activated charcoal and/or osmotic cathartic. Forced diuresis, alkalinization of urine, hemodialysis, or hemoperfusion may not be useful. Manage patients with symptomatic and supportive care.' WHERE MEDID=30;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy to cephalosporin or penicillin antibiotics. Decrease dose in patients with renal insufficiency. May produce false-positive result for glucose in the urine; increase INR with concurrent anticoagulants. Use with probenecid blocks excretion and increases blood levels of antibiotic. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, anaphylaxis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, erythema multiforme, toxic epidermal necrolysis, renal dysfunction, toxic nephropathy, hepatic dysfunction including cholestasis, aplastic anemia, hemolytic anemia, hemorrhage, and pancytopenia have been observed. Seizures have also been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Symptoms of oral overdose may include nausea, vomiting, epigastric distress, diarrhea, and hematuria. Protect the patient airway and support ventilation and perfusion. Meticulously monitor and maintain, within acceptable limits, the patient vital signs, blood gases, serum electrolytes, etc. Absorption of drugs from the gastrointestinal tract may be decreased by giving activated charcoal, which, in many cases, is more effective than emesis or lavage.' WHERE MEDID=31;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to cetirizine or other antihistamine containing hydroxyzine. Monitor liver and kidney function, may require adjusted dose. Use caution with sedatives, hypnotics, alcohol.', INTERACTIONS='Allergic reactions including angioneurotic edema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other serious reactions include cardiac failure, tachycardia, bronchospasm, edema, confusion, ataxia, hallucinations, convulsions, visual changes, weakness, tremors, hepatitis, thrombocytopenia, hemolytic anemia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Should overdose occur, treatment should be symptomatic or supportive, taking into account any concomitantly ingested medications. There is no known specific antidote to Cetirizine hydrochloride. Cetirizine hydrochloride is not effectively removed by dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=32;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy or previous adverse reaction to quinolone antibiotics. Concurrent use with tizanidine or theophylline is contraindicated. Associated with mild to severe central nervous system effects, exacerbation of myasthenia gravis; prolonged QT interval with risk of cardiac arrhythmia and torsades de pointes; moderate to severe phototoxicity reactions. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, anaphylaxis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis, renal failure, hepatic failure, aplastic anemia, hemolytic anemia, thrombocytopenia, and pancytopenia have been observed. Also associated with tendinitis, tendon rupture, central nervous system effects (convulsions, seizures, increased intracranial pressure, toxic psychosis, hallucinations).', SIDE_EFFECTS='In the event of acute overdosage, reversible renal toxicity has been reported in some cases. Empty the stomach by inducing vomiting or by gastric lavage. Observe the patient carefully and give supportive treatment, including monitoring of renal function, urinary pH and acidify, if required, to prevent crystalluria and administration of magnesium, aluminum, or calcium containing antacids which can reduce the absorption of ciprofloxacin. Adequate hydration must be maintained.' WHERE MEDID=33;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to citalopram or concurrent use of MAO inhibitors. May cause QTc prolongation, precipitate manic episode, trigger acute angle closure glaucoma, increased risk of bleeding events, hyponatremia, precipitate a manic episode. Use caution with hepatic impairment. Multiple drug interactions: serotonergic drugs, anticoagulants, NSAIDS, cimetidine, particularly inhibitors or inducers of CYP2C19.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Risk of suicidal thinking and behavior, ventricular tachycardia, sudden death, life-threatening serotonin syndrome, seizures, angina, myocardial infarction, atrial fibrillation cerebrovascular accident, transient ischemic attack, ataxia, hallucination, psychosis, panic reaction, bronchospasm, renal failure, urinary retention, epidermal necrolysis, erythema multiforme, GI hemorrhage, pancreatitis, thrombocytopenia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose symptoms include dizziness, nausea, vomiting, somnolence, sinus tachycardia, confusion, coma, convulsions, hyperventilation, cyanosis, rhabdomyolysis, QTc prolongation, nodal rhythm, ventricular arrhythmia, torsade de pointes, acute renal failure. Ensure an adequate airway, oxygenation, and ventilation. Monitor cardiac rhythm and vital signs. Gastric lavage and activated charcoal are helpful. No specific antidotes. Diuresis, dialysis are unlikely to be of benefit.' WHERE MEDID=34;
