UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to clobetasol. Avoid contact with eyes. Do not cover the treated skin unless directed by the physician. Not recommend for more than 2 weeks use, nor in patients less than 12 years. Systemic absorption of topical corticosteroids can cause adrenal suppression with the potential for glucocorticosteroid insufficiency after withdrawal of treatment. Cushing syndrome, hyperglycemia, and glucosuria can also be produced.', INTERACTIONS='Serious adverse side effects include adrenal suppression.  Local adverse reactions include stinging, cracking, erythema, folliculitis, numbness of fingers, skin atrophy, and telangiectasia. Occlusive dressings increase risk of more serious side effects: acneiform eruptions, hypopigmentation, perioral dermatitis, allergic contact dermatitis, secondary infection, irritation, striae, and miliaria.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in systemic and more pronounced local adverse effects as listed above. Tapered discontinuation and symptomatic treatment is indicated.' WHERE MEDID=37;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to benzodiazepines, significant liver disease, acute narrow angle glaucoma. CNS depressant effects may be markedly increased with concurrent use of other CNS-depressants. Physical dependence with withdrawal symptoms including seizures may occur. May worsen seizures. Use caution with impaired renal function, compromised respiratory function, porphyria. Risk of fetal abnormalities.', INTERACTIONS='Mild allergic reactions have been reported including rash and facial edema. Suicidal behavior and ideation, urinary retention, hemiparesis, slurred speech, thrombocytopenia, profound sedation, respiratory depression, coma, and death have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose results in somnolence, confusion, and coma, with reduced or absent reflexes, respiratory depression, and hypotension. Vomiting should be induced (gastric lavage if unconscious), maintenance of pulmonary ventilation is essential, IV pressor agents may be necessary for hypotension in addition to IV fluids. Flumazenil may be used for reversal of the sedative effects of benzodiazepines (risk of seizure). Value of dialysis has not been determined.' WHERE MEDID=38;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with adverse reaction to clonidine. Discontinue with taper to prevent withdrawal. May worsen AV block; cause sedative effect/dizziness; potentiate depressive effects of alcohol, barbiturates, sedatives. Neuroleptics may induce/exacerbate orthostatic regulation disturbances. Tricyclic antidepressants may reduce hypotensive effect. Monitor heart rate with concurrent drugs affecting sinus node function or AV nodal conduction (digitalis, calcium channel blockers, beta-blockers).', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Bradycardia, congestive heart failure, sinus node arrest, junctional bradycardia, high degree AV block and arrhythmias, hallucinations, and thrombocytopenia have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Initial hypertension, then hypotension, bradycardia, respiratory depression, hypothermia, decreased reflexes, and miosis. Large overdoses: dysrhythmias, apnea, coma, and seizures. No specific antidote. Induction of vomiting is not recommended. Gastric lavage, activated charcoal, cathartic may be beneficial. Supportive car: atropine sulfate, intravenous fluids, vasopressors. Naloxone for management of respiratory depression, hypotension and/or coma. Dialysis is not likely to be helpful.' WHERE MEDID=39;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to clopidogrel or other thienopyridines  and with active bleeding. Decreased antiplatelet function in CYP2C19 poor metabolizers. Increased risk of bleeding. Concurrent use of drugs which inhibit CYP2C19, omeprazole, and esomeprazole will reduce effectiveness. SSRIs and SNRIs increase bleeding risk.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including hypersensitivity reactions, anaphylactoid reactions, serum sickness have occurred. Other serious reactions include thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura, aplastic anemia/pancytopenia, pancreatitis, liver failure, confusion, hallucinations, bronchospasm, interstitial pneumonitis, eosinophilic pneumonia, toxic epidermal necrolysis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, erythema multiforme, vasculitis.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Platelet inhibition by clopidogrel is irreversible and will last for the life of the platelet. Overdose following clopidogrel administration may result in bleeding complications. Symptoms of acute toxicity were vomiting, prostration, difficult breathing, and gastrointestinal hemorrhage. Platelet transfusion may restore clotting ability.' WHERE MEDID=40;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to codeine or acetaminophen, children who are post-op from tonsillectomy/adenoidectomy. Use caution with head injury or other intracranial lesions, acute abdominal conditions, chronic heavy alcohol abusers, severe impairment of renal or hepatic function, hypothyroidism, urethral stricture, Addison disease, or prostatic hypertrophy. May enhance other narcotic analgesics, alcohol, anesthetics, or other CNS depressants.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include acute liver failure, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, and toxic epidermal necrolysis, severe respiratory depression, thrombocytopenia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Toxicity may result from codeine or acetaminophen in overdose. Gastric decontamination with activated charcoal, followed by N-acetylcysteine to decrease absorption of acetaminophen, parenteral naloxone to counteract codeine, oxygen, intravenous fluids, vasopressors, and other supportive measures should be employed.' WHERE MEDID=41;
