UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to diclofenac, aspirin, other NSAIDs, or sulfonamides, in coronary artery bypass graft surgery. Increased risk of cardiovascular thrombotic events, bleeding, ulceration or perforation, liver injury, new or worsening hypertension, hyperkalemia, asthma exacerbation. Do not use in third trimester pregnancy. May mask infection. Multiple drug interactions: anticoagulants, anti-platelet, SSRIs, SNRIs, antihypertensives, diuretics, digoxin.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include stroke, myocardial infarction, arrhythmia, hepatic failure, CHF, edema, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis, drug reaction with eosinophilia and systemic symptoms, thrombocytopenia, aplastic anemia, pancytopenia, GI bleed, acute renal failure.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Symptoms following acute NSAID overdosages have been typically limited to lethargy, drowsiness, nausea, vomiting, and epigastric pain. No specific antidotes. Consider emesis and/or activated charcoal and/or osmotic cathartic. Forced diuresis, alkalinization of urine, hemodialysis, or hemoperfusion may not be useful. Manage patients with symptomatic and supportive care.' WHERE MEDID=48;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to dicyclomine, obstructive uropathy, obstructive GI disease, severe ulcerative colitis, reflux esophagitis, unstable cardiovascular status in acute hemorrhage, glaucoma, myasthenia gravis, infants less than 6 months, nursing mothers. Decreased heat tolerance. Use caution with hepatic or renal disease, CHF, hypertension, CAD, hyperthyroidism, hiatal hernia, autonomic neuropathy, tachyarrhythmia. Avoid anticholinergics.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include seizures, syncope, pulse rate fluctuations, muscular hypotonia, coma, confusion, hallucinations, psychosis, dyspnea, apnea, asphyxia, urinary retention, paralytic ileus, toxic megacolon.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in headache, nausea, vomiting, blurred vision, dilated pupils, hot, dry skin, dizziness, difficulty in swallowing, CNS stimulation, a curare-like action may occur (i.e., neuromuscular blockade leading to muscular weakness and possible paralysis). Treatment should consist of gastric lavage, emetics, and activated charcoal. If indicated, an appropriate parenteral cholinergic agent may be used as an antidote.' WHERE MEDID=49;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to digoxin or other digitalis preparations, and ventricular fibrillation. May cause severe sinus bradycardia, sinoatrial block. Impaired renal function, hypokalemia, hypercalcemia, or hypomagnesemia may predispose to digoxin toxicity resulting in cardiac arrhythmias. Digoxin has a narrow therapeutic index. Assess digoxin levels, serum electrolytes and renal function periodically. Multiple drug interactions.', INTERACTIONS='Allergic reactions including rash and facial edema have occurred.   Serious reactions include arrhythmias, digoxin toxicity, intestinal ischemia, and hemorrhagic necrosis of the intestines, confusion, and mental disturbances (such as anxiety, depression, delirium, and hallucination), thrombocytopenia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose results in nausea, vomiting, hyperkalemia, arrhythmia, dizziness, various CNS disturbances, cardiac arrest, asystole, ventricular fibrillation. Treatment includes activated charcoal, cardiac monitoring, correct hypokalemia and hypomagnesemia. Digoxin Immune Fab has been shown to be 80 to 90% effective in reversing signs and symptoms of digoxin toxicity. Not effectively removed from the body by dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=50;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to diltiazem, sick sinus syndrome, second- or third-degree AV block, hypotension, acute myocardial infarction and pulmonary congestion. Abnormally slow heart rates, worsening of congestive heart failure, symptomatic hypotension, acute hepatic injury have been noted. Monitor renal and hepatic function and adjust dose. Multiple drug interactions, particularly P450 related.', INTERACTIONS='Severe adverse events include angioedema, heart block, bradycardia, congestive heart failure, edema, hepatic injury, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis, leukocytoclastic vasculitis, hallucinations, hemolytic anemia, thrombocytopenia have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose results in bradycardia, hypotension, heart block, and cardiac failure. Appropriate supportive measures should be employed in addition to gastrointestinal decontamination. Bradycardia responds to atropine, as did heart block, although cardiac pacing was also frequently utilized to treat heart block. Fluids and vasopressors were used to maintain blood pressure and in cases of cardiac failure, inotropic agents were administered. Not removed by peritoneal or hemodialysis.' WHERE MEDID=51;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to divalproex, hepatic disease, mitochondrial disorders, urea cycle disorders, concurrent use of topiramate, prophylaxis of migraines in pregnancy. Serum drug levels should be monitored. May cause suicidal behavior/ideation, hepatic injury, pancreatitis, hyperammonemia with or without encephalopathy, hypothermia, somnolence, stimulation of HIV/CMV virus replication. Multiple significant drug interactions. Fetal toxicity.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Hepatic failure, life-threatening pancreatitis, major congenital malformations, fatal hyperammonemic encephalopathy, thrombocytopenia, bleeding disorders, fatal Drug Reaction with Eosinophilia and Systemic Symptoms, also known as Multiorgan Hypersensitivity have also been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in somnolence, heart block, deep coma, and hypernatremia. Hemodialysis may result in significant removal of drug. The benefit of gastric lavage or emesis will vary with the time since ingestion. General supportive measures should be applied with particular attention to the maintenance of adequate urinary output. Naloxone may reverse the CNS depressant effects of overdosage, but may reverse antiepileptic effect.' WHERE MEDID=52;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to donepezil or piperidine derivatives. May cause bradycardia or heart block, significant gastrointestinal adverse reactions including peptic ulcers and bleeding. Use caution with history of asthma or COPD. Potentiates other cholinesterase drugs. Interferes with anticholinergics.', INTERACTIONS='Seizures, confusion, aggression, hallucinations, heart block, hemolytic anemia, hepatitis, neuroleptic malignant syndrome, pancreatitis, urinary retention, rhabdomyolysis, QTc prolongation, and torsade de pointes have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage with cholinesterase inhibitors can result in cholinergic crisis characterized by severe nausea, vomiting, salivation, sweating, bradycardia, hypotension, respiratory depression, collapse convulsions, and death. Tertiary anticholinergics such as atropine may be used as an antidote, but may produce atypical results. It is not known whether donepezil can be removed by dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=53;
