UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy or adverse reaction to ACE inhibitors. Do not co-administer with aliskiren in diabetics. Symptomatic hypotension, hyperkalemia, jaundice, and cough may occur Monitor renal function, potassium, hepatic function, lithium. Patients on diuretics may experience excessive reduction of blood pressure when initiating therapy. Concurrent NSAIDS increase risk of renal failure. Risk of hypoglycemia increased in diabetics. Fetal toxicity.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Stevens-Johnson syndrome, acute renal failure, and liver failure are also reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage is likely to result in hypotension which can be associated with electrolyte disturbances and renal failure. If ingestion is recent, consider activated charcoal and gastric decontamination (e.g., vomiting, gastric lavage). Supportive management should be employed to ensure adequate hydration and to maintain systemic blood pressure. In the case of marked hypotension, infuse physiological saline solution; as needed, consider vasopressors. May be removed from general circulation by hemodialysis.' WHERE MEDID=57;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to enoxaparin, heparin, pork products, or benzyl alcohol; enoxaparin associated thrombocytopenia; or pathological bleeding. Epidural or spinal hematomas may occur in patients undergoing spinal puncture. May cause thrombocytopenia. Discontinue other anticoagulants, platelet inhibitors, salicylates, NSAIDs, dipyridamole, or sulfinpyrazone.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Spinal hematomas, pathological bleeding, and thrombocytopenia have also been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage may lead to hemorrhagic complications. May be neutralized by slow IV injection of protamine sulfate (1% solution). The dose of protamine sulfate should be equal to the dose of enoxaparin injected: 1 mg protamine sulfate neutralizes 1 mg enoxaparin, (if enoxaparin was administered < 8 hours prior). An infusion of 0.5 mg protamine per 1 mg of enoxaparin may be if > 8 hours since enoxaparin injection or if second dose of protamine required.' WHERE MEDID=58;
