UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to fluticasone propionate, salmeterol, milk proteins or as primary treatment for acute episodes of asthma/COPD. Increases the risk of asthma-related deaths. Can produce life threatening paradoxical bronchospasm. Immunosuppressive: monitor for infections. Use caution with cardiovascular and CNS disorders, cP450 inhibitors, MAO inhibitors, beta-blockers.  Associated with adrenal insufficiency, hypokalemia, glaucoma, impaired growth, reduced bone density.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Can produce life threatening paradoxical bronchospasm. Atrial fibrillation, arrhythmias, edema, Cushings syndrome, dyspnea, agitation, and behavioral changes have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Signs of overdosage may include seizures, angina, hypertension or hypotension, tachycardia, arrhythmias, metabolic acidosis, hypokalemia, cardiac arrest and even death. Treatment consists of discontinuation of medication together with appropriate symptomatic and/or supportive therapy. Cardioselective beta-receptor blocker may be considered, but could cause bronchospasm. Cardiac monitoring is recommended.' WHERE MEDID=75;
