UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy or previous adverse reaction to quinolone antibiotics. Associated with mild to severe central nervous system effects, exacerbation of myasthenia gravis; prolonged QT interval with risk of cardiac arrhythmia and torsades de pointes; disturbance of glucose in diabetics, phototoxicity reactions. Antacids and iron supplements interfere with absorption. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, anaphylaxis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis, renal failure, hepatic failure, aplastic anemia, hemolytic anemia, thrombocytopenia, and pancytopenia have been observed. Also associated with tendinitis, tendon rupture, central nervous system effects (convulsions, seizures, increased intracranial pressure, toxic psychosis, hallucinations).', SIDE_EFFECTS='In the event of an acute overdosage, the stomach should be emptied. The patient should be observed and appropriate hydration maintained. Levofloxacin is not efficiently removed by hemodialysis or peritoneal dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=99;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with uncorrected adrenal insufficiency. Do not use for treatment of obesity or weight loss or to treat myxedema coma. Cardiac adverse reactions in the elderly and with underlying cardiovascular disease, acute adrenal crisis in patients with adrenal insufficiency, may worsen glycemic control, decreases bone mineral density. Careful drug monitoring required.', INTERACTIONS='Adverse reactions associated with SYNTHROID therapy are primarily those of hyperthyroidism due to therapeutic overdosage: arrhythmias, myocardial infarction, dyspnea, muscle spasm, headache, nervousness, irritability, insomnia, tremors, muscle weakness, increased appetite, weight loss, diarrhea, heat intolerance, menstrual irregularities, and skin rash.', SIDE_EFFECTS='The signs and symptoms of overdosage are those of hyperthyroidism. In addition, confusion and disorientation, cerebral embolism, seizures, shock, coma, and death have been reported. Initiate appropriate supportive treatment as dictated by the patient medical status.' WHERE MEDID=100;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to liraglutide, with medullary thyroid carcinoma, or with Multiple Endocrine Neoplasia syndrome type 2.  Increases risk of C-cell thyroid cancer, pancreatitis, hypoglycemia, renal failure. Causes delay of gastric emptying, and has the potential to impact the absorption of concomitantly administered oral medications.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include pancreatitis, thyroid carcinoma, renal failure, hepatitis.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose effects have included severe nausea and severe vomiting. In the event of overdosage, appropriate supportive treatment should be initiated according to the patient clinical signs and symptoms.' WHERE MEDID=101;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with: hypersensitivity to amphetamine products; use of MAO concurrently or within the prior 14 days. May cause increase pulse, blood pressure, psychiatric events, cardiovascular events, growth suppression, serotonin syndrome, peripheral vasculopathy. Acidifying agents decrease amphetamine blood levels, while alkalinizing agents increase amphetamine blood levels. Prone to abuse and dependence.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Sudden death, stroke, myocardial, infarction, psychotic or manic symptoms, rhabdomyolysis,  and Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose induces tremor, hyperreflexia, rapid respiration, confusion, hostility, hallucinations, panic states, hyperpyrexia and rhabdomyolysis, arrhythmias, hypertension or hypotension, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea. Fatal poisoning is usually preceded by convulsions and coma. Consider gastric lavage, administration of activated charcoal, and a cathartic. Intensive care must be provided to maintain adequate circulation and respiratory exchange. Amphetamines are not dialyzable.' WHERE MEDID=102;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy or adverse reaction to ACE inhibitors. Do not co-administer with aliskiren in diabetics. Symptomatic hypotension, hyperkalemia, jaundice, and cough may occur Monitor renal function, potassium, hepatic function, lithium. Patients on diuretics may experience excessive reduction of blood pressure when initiating therapy. Concurrent NSAIDS increase risk of renal failure. Risk of hypoglycemia increased in diabetics. Fetal toxicity.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions, including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Stevens-Johnson syndrome, acute renal failure, and liver failure are also reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage is likely to result in hypotension which can be associated with electrolyte disturbances and renal failure. If ingestion is recent, consider activated charcoal and gastric decontamination (e.g., vomiting, gastric lavage). Supportive management should be employed to ensure adequate hydration and to maintain systemic blood pressure. In the case of marked hypotension, infuse physiological saline solution; as needed, consider vasopressors. May be removed from general circulation by hemodialysis.' WHERE MEDID=103;
