UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to loratadine or to desloratadine. Monitor liver and kidney function. Use caution with sedatives, hypnotics, alcohol.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other serious reactions include liver damage, tachycardia, angina, seizures.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Symptoms of an overdose include somnolence, severe headache, extrapyramidal side effects, and tachycardia.  Emesis induction, charcoal slurries as well as gastric lavage should be considered.  Treatment consists of supportive measures to manage and treat the symptoms as they occur. Loratadine cannot be removed by standard dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=105;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to benzodiazepines or acute narrow-angle glaucoma. May cause abnormal thinking and behavior changes. CNS depressant effects may be markedly increased with concurrent use of other CNS-depressants. Physical dependence with withdrawal symptoms including seizures may occur. Use caution with renal or hepatic impairment.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including anaphylaxis have occurred. Suicidal behavior and ideation, ataxia, confusion, amnesia, depression, slurred speech, seizures, coma, visual disturbance, apnea, thrombocytopenia, pancytopenia, profound sedation, respiratory depression, coma, and death have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose results in somnolence, confusion, and coma, with reduced or absent reflexes, respiratory depression, and hypotension. Vomiting should be induced (gastric lavage if unconscious), maintenance of pulmonary ventilation is essential, IV pressor agents may be necessary for hypotension in addition to IV fluids. Flumazenil may be used for reversal of the sedative effects of benzodiazepines (risk of seizure). Value of dialysis has not been determined.' WHERE MEDID=106;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to losartan. Concurrent use with aliskiren contraindicated. Symptomatic hypotension may occur after initiation of treatment. Hyperkalemia and increased lithium have been observed. Concurrent use of NSAIDs may result in deterioration of renal function. Monitor renal function, potassium, lithium. Fetal toxicity.', INTERACTIONS='Severe allergic reactions have occurred including angioedema and anaphylaxis. Renal failure, atrial fibrillation, cerebrovascular accident, thrombocytopenia, rhabdomyolysis, vasculitis, including Henoch-Sch√∂nlein purpura, has been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='The most likely manifestation of overdosage would be hypotension and tachycardia; bradycardia could occur from parasympathetic (vagal) stimulation. If symptomatic hypotension should occur, supportive treatment should be instituted. Neither losartan nor its active metabolite can be removed by hemodialysis.' WHERE MEDID=107;
