UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to lovastatin; active liver disease; concurrent CYP3A4 inhibitors, cyclosporine, or gemfibrozil; pregnancy; nursing mothers. May cause myopathy, rhabdomyolysis, liver dysfunction (monitor enzymes), CNS vascular lesions, increased HbA1c and glucose, optic nerve degeneration. Use caution with concurrent colchicine or CYP3A4 inhibitors.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Rhabdomyolysis leading to renal failure, necrotizing myopathy, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and toxic epidermal necrolysis, hepatic failure, hepatic necrosis, pancreatitis, thrombocytopenia, peripheral nerve palsy, memory impairment, confusion have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='A few cases of accidental overdosage have been reported; no patients had any specific symptoms, and all patients recovered without sequelae. Until further experience is obtained, no specific treatment of overdosage with lovastatin can be recommended. The dialyzability of lovastatin and its metabolites in man is not known at present.' WHERE MEDID=109;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to lurasidone, dementia-related psychosis, concurrently with strong CYP3A4 inhibitors or inducers. May cause metabolic changes that include hyperglycemia/diabetes mellitus, worsen glycemic control in diabetics, orthostatic hypotension, cognitive and motor impairment, dysphagia.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema have occurred. Other serious reactions include suicidal thoughts and behaviors, seizures, stroke, CVA, Neuroleptic Malignant Syndrome, tardive dyskinesia, parkinsonism, extrapyramidal symptoms, heart block, rhabdomyolysis, renal failure.', SIDE_EFFECTS='For overdose: Gastric lavage and activated charcoal with a laxative should be considered. Obtundation, seizures, or dystonic reaction may create a risk of aspiration Cardiovascular monitoring should commence immediately. Hypotension and shock should not be treated with epinephrine, dopamine or other sympathomimetics with beta-agonist activity. In case of severe extrapyramidal symptoms, use anticholinergics. No specific antidote to lurasidone.' WHERE MEDID=110;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to Meclizine. May cause drowsiness. Avoid alcohol. Use caution with asthma, glaucoma or enlargement of the prostate gland.', INTERACTIONS='Anaphylactoid reaction, drowsiness, dry mouth, headache, fatigue, vomiting and, on rare occasions, blurred vision have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Focus on circulatory, respiratory, neurologic systems and frequently monitor vital signs. Administer naloxone and thiamine and assess for hypoglycemia in patients with altered mental status. Manage seizures with benzodiazepines. Physostigmine is not recommended in the prehospital setting. Avoid ipecac syrup and defer administration of activated charcoal unless a prolonged transport time is anticipated.' WHERE MEDID=111;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to meloxicam, aspirin, other NSAIDs, or sulfonamides, in coronary artery bypass graft surgery. Increased risk of cardiovascular thrombotic events, bleeding, ulceration or perforation, liver injury, new or worsening hypertension, hyperkalemia, asthma exacerbation. Do not use in third trimester pregnancy. May mask infection. Multiple drug interactions: anticoagulants, aspirin, ACE inhibitors, diuretics, cholestyramine, lithium.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include stroke, myocardial infarction, arrhythmia, hepatic failure, CHF, edema, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis, thrombocytopenia , GI bleed, acute renal failure, urinary retention.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Symptoms following acute NSAID overdosages have been typically limited to lethargy, drowsiness, nausea, vomiting, and epigastric pain. No specific antidotes. Consider emesis and/or activated charcoal and/or osmotic cathartic. Forced diuresis, alkalinization of urine, hemodialysis, or hemoperfusion may not be useful. Manage patients with symptomatic and supportive care.' WHERE MEDID=112;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to memantine. Conditions that raise urine pH may decrease elimination resulting in increased plasma levels.', INTERACTIONS='Suicidal ideation, pancytopenia, thrombocytopenia, congestive heart failure, hepatitis, acute renal failure, Stevens Johnson syndrome have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage causes agitation, bradycardia, confusion, coma, dizziness, ECG changes, increased blood pressure, loss of consciousness, psychosis, visual hallucinations, vomiting, and weakness. General supportive measures should be utilized, and treatment should be symptomatic. Elimination of memantine can be enhanced by acidification of urine.' WHERE MEDID=113;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to metformin, severe renal impairment, metabolic acidosis. May cause lactic acidosis, particularly with renal impairment, monitor renal function. May cause hypoglycemia. Multiple drug interactions: monitor blood glucose when starting, stopping, or changing medication doses.', INTERACTIONS='Adverse reactions include lactic acidosis resulting in death, hypothermia, hypotension, and resistant bradyarrhythmias; hepatocellular liver injury; palpitation; abdominal pain.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Hypoglycemia and lactic acidosis have been reported in metformin overdose cases. Appropriate supportive treatment should be initiated according to the patient clinical signs and symptoms. Hemodialysis may be useful for removal of accumulated drug from patients in whom metformin overdosage is suspected.' WHERE MEDID=114;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to methadone, respiratory depression, acute bronchial asthma, hypercarbia, gastrointestinal obstruction. Prolongs QT interval. May cause severe hypotension. Use caution with CNS depressants, head injury, increased intracranial pressure, debilitated patients, impaired hepatic or renal function. Multiple drug interactions, particularly CYP 3A4 inhibitors.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include severe respiratory depression, seizures, arrhythmias, life-threatening serotonin syndrome, urinary retention, include acute liver failure, adrenal insufficiency, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, and toxic epidermal necrolysis, thrombocytopenia. Intense opioid withdrawal symptoms may occur.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Manifestations of acute overdose include respiratory depression, somnolence progressing to stupor or coma, constricted pupils, pulmonary edema, bradycardia, hypotension, partial or complete airway obstruction, and death. Establish protected airway, for significant respiratory or circulatory depression administer an opioid antagonist. Cardiac arrest or arrhythmias will require advanced life-support techniques.' WHERE MEDID=115;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to methocarbamol. Use caution with concurrent CNS depressants, myasthenia gravis patients receiving anticholinesterases.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioneurotic and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include hypotension, syncope, bradycardia, confusion, sedation, seizures.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in nausea, drowsiness, blurred vision, hypotension, seizures, and coma. Supportive measures include maintenance of an adequate airway, monitoring urinary output and vital signs, and administration of intravenous fluids if necessary. The usefulness of hemodialysis in managing overdose is unknown.' WHERE MEDID=116;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to methotrexate, preexisting blood dyscrasias, evidence of immunodeficiency syndromes, alcoholism, alcoholic liver disease or other chronic liver disease, nursing mothers, pregnancy. Reduce dosage in impaired renal function, ascites, or pleural effusions. May induce tumor lysis syndrome. Concurrent radiotherapy has risk of soft tissue necrosis and osteonecrosis. Use with NSAIDS may be fatal at higher doses.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including anaphylaxis have occurred. Fetal death and/or congenital anomalies, enteritis and death from intestinal perforation, malignant lymphoma, fatal opportunistic infections, thromboembolic events, hepatotoxicity, fibrosis and cirrhosis, aplastic anemia, pancytopenia, thrombocytopenia, nonspecific pneumonitis, acute renal failure, toxic epidermal necrolysis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and erythema multiforme, paresis, convulsions, encephalopathy have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Leucovorin is indicated to diminish the toxicity and counteract the effect of inadvertently administered overdosages of methotrexate. Hydration and urinary alkalinization may be necessary to prevent the precipitation of methotrexate and/or its metabolites in the renal tubules. Neither hemodialysis nor peritoneal dialysis have been shown to improve methotrexate elimination.' WHERE MEDID=117;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with: hypersensitivity to Concerta; marked anxiety, tension, or agitation; use of MAO concurrently or within the prior 14 days; Tourette; or glaucoma. May cause increase pulse, blood pressure, psychiatric events, cardiovascular events, priapism, visual disturbances, growth suppression, intestinal obstruction. Monitor CBC during prolonged therapy. Inhibits metabolism of coumadin, anticonvulsants, and some antidepressants. Prone to abuse and dependence.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Sudden death, stroke, myocardial,  infarction, psychotic or manic symptoms, hostility, seizures, pancytopenia, thrombocytopenia,  and liver failure have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose results in vomiting, agitation, twitching, convulsion, confusion, hallucinations, hyperhidrosis, headache, pyrexia, tachycardia, palpitations, tachycardia, sinus arrhythmia, hypertension, rhabdomyolysis, mydriasis, and dry mouth. Consider gastric lavage, administration of activated charcoal, and a cathartic. Intensive care must be provided to maintain adequate circulation and respiratory exchange; external cooling procedures may be required for pyrexia.' WHERE MEDID=118;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to methylprednisolone or systemic fungal infection. May mask signs of infection. Stress requires increased dose. Concurrent vaccinations produce increased risk of neurological complications and lack of antibody response. Increased risk of serious infections. Use caution with hypothyroidism, renal or hepatic impairment, psychotic tendencies, myasthenia gravis, hypertension.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include posterior subcapsular cataracts, glaucoma with possible damage to the optic nerves, drug-induced secondary adrenocortical and pituitary insufficiency, psychotic manifestations, convulsions, increased intracranial pressure, CHF, hypertension, osteoporosis with pathologic fractures, pancreatitis, peptic/esophageal ulcers with perforation.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Treatment of acute overdosage is by supportive and symptomatic therapy. For chronic overdosage in the face of severe disease requiring continuous steroid therapy, the dosage of corticosteroid may be reduced only temporarily, or alternate day treatment may be introduced.' WHERE MEDID=119;
