UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to metoprolol, severe bradycardia, heart block greater than first degree, cardiogenic shock, decompensated cardiac failure, sick sinus syndrome. Use extreme caution with bronchospastic diseases, pheochromocytoma, diabetes, hyperthyroidism, peripheral vascular disease, calcium channel blockers, hepatic impairment, catecholamine-depleting drugs, inhibitors of CYP2D6 (quinidine), digoxin, clonidine.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Abrupt cessation of therapy may cause exacerbations of angina pectoris and, in some cases, myocardial infarction. Other adverse reactions include intensification of AV block, CHF, edema, bradycardia, chest pain, dyspnea, Peyronie disease, catatonia, hallucinations, hepatitis, thrombocytopenia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may cause severe hypotension, sinus bradycardia, atrioventricular block, heart failure, cardiogenic shock, cardiac arrest, bronchospasm, impairment of consciousness/coma, and cyanosis. Patients with myocardial infarction or CHF should be treated under intensive care conditions. Gastric lavage, atropine for bradycardia, vasopressor for hypotension, beta2-stimulating agent and/or a theophylline for bronchospasm, digitalis glycoside and diuretics for cardiac failure.' WHERE MEDID=121;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy or previous reaction to metronidazole or other nitroimidazole derivatives. Do not use in patients who have taken disulfiram within the last two weeks. Discontinue consumption of alcohol for at least three days after therapy. Reduce dosage in hepatic and renal impairment. Increased INR in patients taking anticoagulants; increase lithium levels. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis.', INTERACTIONS='Convulsive seizures, encephalopathy, aseptic meningitis, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose symptoms reported include nausea, vomiting, and ataxia. Neurotoxic effects, including seizures and peripheral neuropathy, have been reported. There is no specific antidote for metronidazole overdose; therefore, management of the patient should consist of symptomatic and supportive therapy.' WHERE MEDID=122;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy or previous reaction to tetracyclines antibiotics. Concurrent use of isotretinoin is contraindicated. May potentiate anticoagulants. Monitor creatinine and BUN. Antacids and iron supplements interfere with absorption. Noted to cause photosensitivity, dizziness and vertigo. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis. Fetal toxicity.', INTERACTIONS='Anaphylaxis, Drug Rash with Eosinophilia and Systemic Symptoms (DRESS) including fatal cases, toxic epidermal necrolysis, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, intracranial hypertension, liver failure, renal failure, hemolytic anemia, pancytopenia, transient lupus-like syndrome and serum sickness-like reactions also have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='The adverse events more commonly seen in overdose are dizziness, nausea, and vomiting. No specific antidote for minocycline is known. In case of overdosage, discontinue medication, treat symptomatically, and institute supportive measures. Minocycline is not removed in significant quantities by hemodialysis or peritoneal dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=123;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to mirtazapine or concurrent use of MAO inhibitors. May trigger acute angle closure glaucoma, cause hyponatremia, somnolence, increased liver enzymes, or precipitate a manic episode. Multiple drug interactions: serotonergic drugs, triptans, particularly drugs metabolized and/or inhibit P450 enzymes.', INTERACTIONS='Risk of suicidal thinking and behavior, life-threatening serotonin syndrome, QT prolongation, Torsades de Pointes, ventricular tachycardia, and sudden death, seizures, arrhythmia, myocardial infarction, pulmonary embolus, cerebral ischemia, pancreatitis, thrombocytopenia, fracture, ataxia, hallucinations, paralysis, urinary retention, rhabdomyolysis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, erythema multiforme and toxic epidermal necrolysis.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose symptoms include disorientation, drowsiness, impaired memory, and tachycardia; QT prolongation and Torsades de Pointes have been reported. Ensure an adequate airway, oxygenation, ventilation, monitor ECG and vital signs. Gastric lavage and activated charcoal are helpful. No specific antidotes. Diuresis, dialysis are unlikely to be of benefit.' WHERE MEDID=124;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to mometasone furoate. Increase risk of epistaxis, nasal ulceration, fungal infection, septal perforation, impaired wound healing, glaucoma and/or cataracts. Hypercorticism and adrenal suppression may appear. Increased risk of infection, more serious or even fatal course. Use caution with concurrent ketoconazole.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Nasal ulcerations, septal perforation, fungal infection, cataracts, glaucoma, and immunosuppression with fulminant infections have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Chronic overdosage may result in signs/symptoms of hypercorticism. Acute overdosage with the intranasal dosage form is unlikely due to low systemic bioavailability and limited product in bottle.' WHERE MEDID=125;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to montelukast. Not indicated for use in the reversal of bronchospasm. May cause neuropsychiatric events or systemic eosinophilia.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioneurotic edema have occurred. Other serious reactions include seizures, hostility, hallucinations, suicidal thinking and behavior, thrombocytopenia, pancreatitis, liver injury, pulmonary eosinophilia, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis.', SIDE_EFFECTS='In the event of overdose, it is reasonable to employ the usual supportive measures; e.g., remove unabsorbed material from the gastrointestinal tract, employ clinical monitoring, and institute supportive therapy, if required. It is not known whether montelukast is removed by dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=126;
