UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to nebivolol, Severe bradycardia, heart block, cardiogenic shock, decompensated cardiac failure, sick sinus syndrome, severe hepatic impairment. Use extreme caution in bronchospastic disorders, diabetes, hyperthyroidism, calcium channel blockers, CYP2D6 inhibitors, impaired renal or hepatic function, digoxin, other beta blockers, pheochromocytoma.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Abrupt discontinuation in patients with coronary artery disease may cause severe exacerbation of angina, myocardial infarction and ventricular arrhythmias. Other adverse reactions include acute pulmonary edema, acute renal failure, atrioventricular block, bronchospasm, myocardial infarction, peripheral ischemia/claudication, thrombocytopenia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may cause severe hypotension, sinus bradycardia, atrioventricular block, heart failure, cardiogenic shock, cardiac arrest, bronchospasm, impairment of consciousness/coma, and cyanosis. Hemodialysis is not effective. Atropine for bradycardia, IV fluids and vasopressor for hypotension, isoproterenol for heart block, beta2-stimulating agent and/or a theophylline for bronchospasm, digitalis glycoside and diuretics for cardiac failure.' WHERE MEDID=130;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to nifedipine. Worsening angina and acute myocardial infarction can develop after starting or increasing dose, particularly in severe obstructive coronary artery disease. Severe hypotension and/or increased fluid volume requirement, worsening of congestive heart failure, serious gastrointestinal obstruction or ulceration have been reported. Concurrent use with CYP3A inhibitors (moderate and strong) results in increased levels, may require dose reduction.', INTERACTIONS='Severe adverse events include severe hypotension, congestive heart failure, tachycardia, angina, myocardial infarction, peripheral ischemia, syncope, dyspnea, gastrointestinal obstruction, allergic reaction, erythema multiforme, toxic epidermal necrolysis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and hyperglycemia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage leads to pronounced hypotension requiring active cardiovascular support, including monitoring of cardiovascular and respiratory function, elevation of extremities, judicious use of calcium infusion, pressor agents, and fluids. Clearance of nifedipine would be expected to be prolonged in patients with impaired liver function. Since nifedipine is highly protein-bound, dialysis is not likely to be of any benefit.' WHERE MEDID=131;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with allergy or previous reaction to nitrofurantoin. Contraindicated in impaired renal function, pregnant patients, and neonates. Monitor for liver injury. Antacids interfere with absorption. Use with probenecid blocks excretion and increases blood levels of antibiotic. May produce false-positive result for glucose in the urine. Clostridium difficile associated diarrhea has been reported, ranging from mild diarrhea to fatal colitis.', INTERACTIONS='Systemic allergic reactions, including anaphylaxis and angioedema have occurred. Liver necrosis, intracranial hypertension, acute pulmonary hypersensitivity reaction, and hemolytic anemia in patients with glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase(G6PD) deficiency have also been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Occasional incidents of acute overdosage of nitrofurantoin have not resulted in any specific symptoms other than vomiting. Induction of emesis is recommended. There is no specific antidote, but a high fluid intake should be maintained to promote urinary excretion of the drug. Nitrofurantoin is dialyzable.' WHERE MEDID=132;
