UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to rivastigmine or other carbamate derivatives. Significant gastrointestinal adverse reactions including nausea, vomiting, peptic ulcers and bleeding; allergic dermatitis; extrapyramidal symptoms (potentiated by concurrent metoclopramide); brady cardia (potentiated by concurrent beta-blockers) may occur. Use caution with history of asthma or COPD. Potentiates other cholinesterase drugs. Interferes with anticholinergics.', INTERACTIONS='Hepatitis, aggression, seizures, urinary retention, Stevens Johnson syndrome have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage with cholinesterase inhibitors can result in cholinergic crisis characterized by severe nausea, vomiting, salivation, sweating, bradycardia, hypotension, respiratory depression, collapse convulsions, and death. Tertiary anticholinergics such as atropine may be used as an antidote for overdosage, but may produce atypical results. Due to the short half-life of rivastigmine, dialysis would not be clinically indicated in the event of an overdose.' WHERE MEDID=167;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to ropinirole. May cause somnolence, syncope, bradycardia, orthostatic hypotension, exacerbation of psychosis or dyskinesia, increased risk of melanoma, fibrotic complications including retroperitoneal fibrosis, pulmonary infiltrates, pleural effusion, pleural thickening, pericarditis, and cardiac valvulopathy. Drug interactions with dopamine antagonists, estrogens, and CYP1A2 inhibitors and inducers.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include hallucinations, psychotic behavior, compulsive behavior, peripheral ischemia.  May cause neuroleptic malignant syndrome with abrupt withdrawal.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in visual hallucinations, hyperhidrosis, claustrophobia, chorea, palpitations, asthenia, and nightmares. Additional symptoms reported in cases of overdose included vomiting, increased coughing, fatigue, syncope, vasovagal syncope, dyskinesia, agitation, chest pain, orthostatic hypotension, somnolence, and confusional state. General supportive measures are recommended. Vital signs should be maintained, if necessary.' WHERE MEDID=168;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to rosuvastatin, active liver disease, concurrent gemfibrozil, pregnancy, nursing mothers. May cause myopathy, rhabdomyolysis, liver dysfunction (monitor enzymes), increased HbA1c and glucose, proteinuria and hematuria. Use caution with concurrent cyclosporine, colchicine, or coumadin (monitor INR).', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema. Rhabdomyolysis leading to renal failure, necrotizing myopathy, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and toxic epidermal necrolysis, hepatic failure, pancreatitis, thrombocytopenia, memory impairment, confusion have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='There is no specific treatment in the event of overdose. In the event of overdose, the patient should be treated symptomatically and supportive measures instituted as required. Hemodialysis does not significantly enhance clearance of rosuvastatin.' WHERE MEDID=169;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to saxagliptin. May cause pancreatitis, hypoglycemia, severe and disabling arthralgia, bullous pemphigoid, exacerbate heart failure. Strong CYP3A inhibitors increase potential for hypoglycemia.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include congestive heart failure, pancreatitis, severe arthralgias, bullous pemphigoid.', SIDE_EFFECTS='In the event of an overdose, appropriate supportive treatment should be initiated as dictated by the patient clinical status. Saxagliptin and its active metabolite are removed by hemodialysis.' WHERE MEDID=170;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to sertraline or concurrent use of MAO inhibitors. May precipitate manic episode, increase risk of bleeding, hyponatremia. Use caution with liver impairment. Multiple drug interactions: serotonergic drugs, triptans, anticoagulants, NSAIDS, cimetidine, sumatriptan, particularly drugs metabolized by P450.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Risk of suicidal thinking and behavior, life-threatening serotonin syndrome or Neuroleptic Malignant Syndrome, seizures, priapism, myocardial infarction, cerebrovascular disorder, ataxia, hallucination, aggression, extrapyramidal symptoms, bronchospasm, renal failure, visual changes, aplastic anemia, pancytopenia, thrombocytopenia, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, vasculitis, liver failure.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage may result in somnolence, vomiting, bundle branch block, coma, convulsions, delirium, hallucinations, hypertension, hypotension, manic reaction, pancreatitis, QT-interval prolongation, serotonin syndrome, stupor and syncope. Ensure an adequate airway, oxygenation and ventilation. Gastric lavage, activated charcoal are helpful. No specific antidotes. Diuresis, dialysis are unlikely to be of benefit.' WHERE MEDID=171;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to sildenafil, concurrent use with nitrates or GC stimulators (riociguat). Potential cardiac risk of sexual activity in patients with cardiovascular disease.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Angina, AV block, heart failure, cardiac arrest, arrhythmia, sudden cardiac death, seizures, cerebral hemorrhage, cerebral thrombosis, pulmonary hemorrhage, hearing loss, vision loss, ataxia, vertigo, exfoliative dermatitis have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Adverse events with overdose were similar to those seen at lower doses but incidence rates and severities were increased. In cases of overdose, standard supportive measures should be adopted as required. Renal dialysis is not expected to accelerate clearance as sildenafil is highly bound to plasma proteins and it is not eliminated in the urine.' WHERE MEDID=172;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to simvastatin; active liver disease; concurrent CYP3A4 inhibitors, gemfibrozil, cyclosporine, or danazol; pregnancy; nursing mothers. May cause myopathy, rhabdomyolysis, liver dysfunction (monitor enzymes), increased HbA1c and glucose. Use caution with concurrent coumadin (monitor INR).', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Rhabdomyolysis leading to renal failure, necrotizing myopathy, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and toxic epidermal necrolysis, interstitial lung disease, hepatic failure, pancreatitis, hemolytic anemia, thrombocytopenia, memory impairment, confusion have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Few cases of overdosage have been reported. All patients recovered without sequelae. Supportive measures should be taken in the event of an overdose. The dialyzability of simvastatin and its metabolites in man is not known at present.' WHERE MEDID=173;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to sitagliptin. May cause pancreatitis, hypoglycemia, severe and disabling arthralgia, bullous pemphigoid. Monitor renal function and adjust dose.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include Stevens-Johnson syndrome, renal failure, pancreatitis, severe arthralgia.', SIDE_EFFECTS='For overdose, employ the l supportive measures, remove unabsorbed material from the gastrointestinal tract, employ clinical monitoring (including obtaining an electrocardiogram), and institute supportive therapy as dictated by the patient clinical status. Sitagliptin is modestly dialyzable.' WHERE MEDID=174;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to solifenacin, urinary retention, gastric retention, severe decreased GI motility conditions, uncontrolled narrow-angle glaucoma. May cause CNS anticholinergic effects. Use caution with renal or hepatic impairment. Use caution with concurrent potent CYP3A4 inhibitors (ketoconazole).', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include urinary retention, renal impairment, QT interval prolongation, Torsade de Pointes, atrial fibrillation, GI obstruction, edema, confusion, hallucinations, erythema multiforme, glaucoma.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in anticholinergic effects including central nervous system excitation, flushing, fever, dehydration, cardiac arrhythmia, vomiting, and urinary retention.  Activated charcoal as well as a cathartic may be administered. Treatment should be symptomatic and supportive. ECG monitoring is also recommended.' WHERE MEDID=175;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to spironolactone, anuria, acute renal insufficiency, significant impairment of renal excretory function, hyperkalemia, Addison disease, and with concomitant use of eplerenone. Avoid potassium supplementation, ACE inhibitors, NSAIDs, aldosterone blockers, angiotension II antagonists - high risk for fatal hyperkalemia. Monitor electrolytes. Avoid lithium, reduce digoxin. Use caution with renal or hepatic impairment.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include hepatic coma, thrombocytopenia , vasculitis , GI bleeding, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis, drug rash with eosinophilia and systemic symptoms.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Acute overdosage of spironolactone may be manifested by drowsiness, mental confusion, maculopapular or erythematous rash, nausea, vomiting, dizziness, diarrhea, hyponatremia, hyperkalemia, or hepatic coma. Induce vomiting or evacuate the stomach by lavage. There is no specific antidote. Treatment is supportive to maintain hydration, electrolyte balance, and vital functions. Persistent hyperkalemia may require dialysis.' WHERE MEDID=176;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to sumatriptan, coronary artery disease, arrhythmias, history of stroke, TIA, hemiplegic or basilar migraine, peripheral vascular disease, ischemic bowel disease, uncontrolled hypertension, concurrent or recent use of monoamine oxidase inhibitor, severe hepatic impairment, recent use of ergotamine-containing or ergot-type medication (dihydroergotamine or methysergide). May cause serotonin syndrome, hypertension, seizures, vasospasm reactions.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred.   Angina, myocardial ischemia and infarction, arrhythmias, cerebrovascular events, peripheral vascular ischemia, gastrointestinal vascular ischemia and infarction, splenic infarction, transient and permanent blindness, seizures, chest, throat, neck, and/or jaw pain/tightness/pressure have been noted.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose in animals has been fatal with convulsions, tremor, paralysis, inactivity, ptosis, erythema of the extremities, abnormal respiration, cyanosis, ataxia, mydriasis, salivation, and lacrimation. The elimination half-life of sumatriptan is approximately 2.5 hours, therefore monitoring of patients after overdose should continue for at least 12 hours or while symptoms or signs persist. It is unknown what effect hemodialysis or peritoneal dialysis has on the serum concentrations.' WHERE MEDID=177;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to tadalafil, concurrent use with nitrates or GC stimulators (riociguat). Potential cardiac risk of sexual activity in patients with cardiovascular disease. Risk of prolonged erection/priapism. May cause sudden loss of vision in one or both eyes or hearing loss. Hypotension reported with concurrent alpha-blockers and other antihypertensives. Decrease dose in renal/hepatic impairment. CYP3A4 inhibitors increase drug level; CYP3A4 potentiator increase level.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Angina, myocardial infarction, sudden cardiac death, stroke, seizure, hearing loss, vision loss, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and exfoliative dermatitis have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Adverse events with overdose were similar to those seen at lower doses. In cases of overdose, standard supportive measures should be adopted as required. Hemodialysis contributes negligibly to tadalafil elimination.' WHERE MEDID=178;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to tamsulosin. Hypotension, vertigo, syncope, and priapism may occur. Use with caution with sulfa allergy, in combination with cimetidine, or with inhibitors of CYP3A4 (erythromycin) or CYP2D6 (paroxetine, terbinafine). Do not use with other alpha drenergic blockers. Intraoperative Floppy Iris Syndrome has occured in cataract surgery in patients on or previously treated with alpha1 blockers. Prostate carcinoma may mimic BPH and should be excluded.', INTERACTIONS='Moderate to severe allergic reactions have occurred including angioedema and respiratory distress. Hypotension, atrial fibrillation, arrhythmia, tachycardia, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, and erythema multiforme have also been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdosage would most likely result in hypotension. Restoration of blood pressure and normalization of heart rate may be accomplished by keeping the patient in the supine position. If this measure is inadequate, administration of IV fluids should be considered. Vasopressors may be necessary. Renal function should be monitored and supported as needed. Tamsulosin is primarily protein bound, therefore, dialysis is unlikely to be of benefit.' WHERE MEDID=179;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to benzodiazepines or women who are or may become pregnant. May cause abnormal thinking and behavior changes. Physical dependence with withdrawal symptoms including seizures may occur. CNS depressant effects may be markedly increased with concurrent use of other CNS-depressants. Use caution with renal or hepatic impairment.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Suicidal behavior and ideation, ataxia, hallucinations, and agitation, profound sedation, respiratory depression, coma, and death have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose results in somnolence, confusion, and coma, with reduced or absent reflexes, respiratory depression, and hypotension. Vomiting should be induced (gastric lavage if unconscious), maintenance of pulmonary ventilation is essential, IV pressor agents may be necessary for hypotension in addition to IV fluids. Flumazenil may be used for reversal of the sedative effects of benzodiazepines (risk of seizure). Value of dialysis has not been determined.' WHERE MEDID=180;
