UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in men with carcinoma of the breast or known or suspected carcinoma of the prostate and women who are or may become pregnant, or who are breastfeeding. May worsen BPH, cause edema, increase risk of prostate cancer, and increase red cells (monitor hematocrit). Some reports of increased cardiovascular risk. Monitor calcium levels and lipids. May decrease blood glucose, interfere with oral anticoagulants.', INTERACTIONS='Moderate allergic reactions including rash, dyspnea, and edema have occurred. Deep venous thrombosis, pulmonary embolism, myocardial infarction, stroke, prostate cancer, abnormal liver function, and hypertension have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Treatment of overdosage would consist of discontinuation of drug, washing the application site with soap and water, and appropriate symptomatic and supportive care.' WHERE MEDID=182;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to ticagrelor, history of intracranial hemorrhage, active bleeding. Increased risk of bleeding. Concurrent use of aspirin decreases effectiveness. Drug interactions, particularly with CYP3A inhibitors/inducers, digoxin. Use caution with hepatic impairment. Elevates serum creatinine.', INTERACTIONS='Serious reactions including life threatening bleeding, dyspnea, and bradyarrhythmias have occurred.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Effects of overdose may include gastrointestinal effects (nausea, vomiting, diarrhea) or ventricular pauses in addition to bleeding. Monitor the ECG. There is no known treatment to reverse the effects of ticagrelor.  Not dialyzable. Platelet transfusion unlikely to be of clinical benefit in patients with bleeding. If bleeding occurs, appropriate supportive measures should be taken.' WHERE MEDID=183;
