UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Rapid withdrawal may cause seizures. May cause acute myopia associated with secondary angle closure glaucoma, visual field defects, decreased sweating with hyperthermia, metabolic acidosis, suicidal behavior/ideation, cognitive/neuropsychiatric adverse reactions, hyperammonemia with or without encephalopathy, and kidney stones. Multiple drug interactions including other antiepiletics, lithium, oral contraceptives, other carbonic anhydrase inhibitors, HCTZ, amitriptyline. Fetal toxicity.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions have not been reported. Increased risk for bleeding, hepatic failure, pancreatitis, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis have occurred.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose may result in convulsions, drowsiness, speech disturbance, blurred vision, diplopia, impaired mentation, lethargy, abnormal coordination, stupor, hypotension, abdominal pain, agitation, dizziness, depression, and severe metabolic acidosis. If the ingestion is recent, the stomach should be emptied immediately by lavage or by induction of emesis. Activated charcoal has been shown to adsorb topiramate in vitro. Hemodialysis is an effective means of removing topiramate from the body.' WHERE MEDID=187;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to tramadol or opioids, acute or severe bronchial asthma, respiratory depression, gastrointestinal obstruction. Use caution with concurrent CNS depressants, MAO inhibitors, SSRIs, head injury, intracranial lesions, impaired hepatic or renal function. Concurrent use or discontinuation of P450 3A4 inhibitors and inducers may cause fatal reaction.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include seizures, life-threatening serotonin syndrome, urinary retention, include acute liver failure, adrenal insufficiency, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome, and toxic epidermal necrolysis, thrombocytopenia. Opioid withdrawal symptoms may occur.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Serious consequences of overdosage are respiratory depression, lethargy, coma, seizure, cardiac arrest and death. Fatalities have been. In treating an overdose, primary attention should be given to maintaining adequate ventilation along with general supportive treatment. While naloxone will reverse some, but not all, symptoms caused by overdosage with tramadol hydrochloride, the risk of seizures is also increased.' WHERE MEDID=188;
