UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to trazodone and during the initial recovery phase of myocardial infarction. May cause hypotension and syncope. Drug interactions, particularly with CYP3A4 inhibitors, carbamazepine, digoxin, phenytoin. Interaction with MAO inhibitors is unknown.', INTERACTIONS='Risk of suicidal thinking and behavior, hallucinations/delusions, ataxia, psychosis, CVA, seizures, congestive heart failure, conduction block, atrial fibrillation, arrhythmia, myocardial infarction, hemolytic anemia, priapism, urinary retention, urticaria.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose of trazodone alone have been priapism, respiratory arrest, seizures, and EKG changes. The reactions reported most frequently have been drowsiness and vomiting. There is no specific antidote for trazodone. Treatment should be symptomatic and supportive in the case of hypotension or excessive sedation. Gastric lavage and forced diuresis may be useful in facilitating elimination of the drug.' WHERE MEDID=190;
