UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to Dyazide or other sulfonamide-derived drugs, preexisting elevated serum potassium, anuria, acute and chronic renal insufficiency, receiving other potassium sparing agents, potassium supplementation. May cause life threating hyperkalemia; hyperglycemia, glycosuria, or alter insulin requirements. Use caution with hepatic failure, heart failure, history of renal stones, ACE inhibitors. Monitor electrolytes. Avoid lithium.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including anaphylaxis have occurred. Other adverse reactions include acute angle-closure glaucoma, lupus erythematosus-like reactions, arrhythmia, pancreatitis, acute renal failure, interstitial nephritis, thrombocytopenia, aplastic anemia, hemolytic anemia pulmonary edema, necrotizing vasculitis, erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Overdose symptoms d include: polyuria, nausea, vomiting, weakness, lassitude, fever, flushed face, and hyperactive deep tendon reflexes. Electrolyte imbalance is the major concern. Induce immediate evacuation of the stomach through emesis or gastric lavage. There is no specific antidote. There may be some benefit to dialysis in cases of overdosage.' WHERE MEDID=192;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to acyclovir or valacyclovir. Dosage adjustment required for impaired renal function. Maintain hydration. Mental status changes are known to occur and may be marked, particularly in older adults or in patients with renal impairment.', INTERACTIONS='Serious allergic reactions including angioedema and anaphylaxis have occurred. Seizures, hallucinations, agitation, confusion, coma, encephalopathy, dyspnea, thrombocytopenia, aplastic anemia, hepatitis, renal failure, erythema multiforme have been noted. Thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura/hemolytic uremic syndrome, resulting in death, has occurred in immunocompromised patients.', SIDE_EFFECTS='Precipitation in renal tubules may occur. Patient may benefit from hemodialysis until renal function is restored.' WHERE MEDID=193;
UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in patients with hypersensitivity to Irbesartan. Concurrent use with aliskiren contraindicated. Symptomatic hypotension may occur after initiation of treatment. Hyperkalemia and increased lithium have been observed. Concurrent use of NSAIDs may result in deterioration of renal function. Monitor renal function, potassium, lithium. Fetal toxicity.', INTERACTIONS='Angioedema, hypersensitivity reactions, vasculitis, rhabdomyolysis, renal failure, liver injury, hepatitis, thrombocytopenia have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='The most likely manifestations of overdosage are expected to be hypotension and tachycardia; bradycardia might also occur from overdose. Depressed level of consciousness, circulatory collapse and shock have been reported. If symptomatic hypotension should occur, supportive treatment should be instituted. Valsartan is not removed by hemodialysis.' WHERE MEDID=194;
