UPDATE MEDICATIONS SET WARNINGS='Contraindicated in severe left ventricular dysfunction, hypotension, cardiogenic shock, sick sinus syndrome, second- or third-degree AV block, atrial flutter or atrial fibrillation and an accessory bypass tract. Symptomatic hypotension, worsening of congestive heart failure, hepatocellular injury, ventricular fibrillation, first-degree AV block, progressive development to second- or third-degree AV block have been reported. Multiple drug interactions, particularly CYP3A4 related.', INTERACTIONS='Severe adverse events include severe hypotension, heart block, congestive heart failure, pulmonary edema, ventricular fibrillation, sinus arrest, myocardial infarction, CVA, confusion, psychotic symptoms, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, erythema multiforme have been reported.', SIDE_EFFECTS='No specific antidote for verapamil overdosage; treatment is supportive. Effects include hypotension, bradycardia, conduction defects, arrhythmias, hyperglycemia, noncardiogenic pulmonary edema, and decreased mental status. Consider cathartics and whole bowel irrigation. Calcium, inotropes, atropine sulfate, vasopressors, and cardiac pacing have been used with variable results to reverse hypotension and myocardial depression. Cannot be removed by hemodialysis.' WHERE MEDID=197;
